(1024, 163, 'single_page_content', 'Democratisation of Spending\r\nWidening spectrum of technology buyers\r\nDisruption of the value Chains and Vertical boundaries\r\n\r\n“Nearly 55% of the time is spent by the sales teams in researching, segmenting, prospecting and shortlisting of opportunities for the sales pitch. The process is often challenging and is usually attempted with limited parameters and partial analysis.”\r\nA potential way to bridge this gap is to drive insights by leveraging technology on a large volume of unstructured data in a contextualized environment in real-time. Such a platform helps identifying “the right customer with the right solution at the right time”. Zinnov calls this the Knowledge Enablement Platform.\r\nZinnov’s DRAUP platform brings together human intelligence, machine intelligence and years of consulting expertise on data sets to provide a multi-dimensional view for sales enablement. It is powered by a team of analysts adding their learning-based insights to the machine-generated insights and models to provide knowledge about companies, executives, and the associated ecosystem3. Unlike other platforms which run on data points, DRAUP derives intelligence by analysing data sets and application of behavioural aspects of executives and organizations.'),
